The paper discusses the creative potential of papers and their cited references in the field of scientometrics, which involves the study of scientific publications and their impact. This topic is relevant to several sub-categories of computer science, including social and information sciences (cs.SI), digital libraries (cs.DL), information retrieval (cs.IR), human-computer interaction (cs.HC), and computers and society (cs.CY). The study also involves case studies and interviews with authors, which suggests a qualitative research approach that is common in social and information sciences.
